tweet: @FinchinABQ Right! It’s self-fulfilling because if you prefer to read, you’re going to do more of it, so you have the illusion that you learn more that way than listening. But it’s not true, you just chose what you liked better! Which is fine, but it’s not a fixed ability.

description: Agender lesbian menace. "The Last Starfighter" superfan. #ActuallyAutistic (she/her)
tweet: Last tip: don’t treat it as homework. Treat it like you’re the most awesome teacher of all time, the one you wish you had as a kid, and you’ve got a classroom of one: yourself. Make your own learning fun and multifaceted and do it just because you deserve it. 💕

name: Julia Gulia 🏳️‍⚧️🏳️‍🌈
description: Agender lesbian menace. "The Last Starfighter" superfan. #ActuallyAutistic (she/her)
tweet: Take advantage of multimedia. Watch videos, look up photos, find songs written about the topic. Spoiler: you can find a lot of great bonus features in the appendix or recommended reading at the back of the book.

name: Julia Gulia 🏳️‍⚧️🏳️‍🌈
description: Agender lesbian menace. "The Last Starfighter" superfan. #ActuallyAutistic (she/her)
tweet: Use all your senses. If it’s your book, write in it! Argue in the margins, underline, draw hearts or winking emojis. If it’s not your book, use a hunk of paper as a bookmark and draw/write there. Make up and sing a jingle to sell the book.

name: Julia Gulia 🏳️‍⚧️🏳️‍🌈
description: Agender lesbian menace. "The Last Starfighter" superfan. #ActuallyAutistic (she/her)
tweet: Don’t let what you’re learning stop with you: bring it into your life. Explain it to someone else (even pets or houseplants work!). Ask them what they think (can’t guarantee results with pets or houseplants here). Draw parallels with things you observe around you.

name: Julia Gulia 🏳️‍⚧️🏳️‍🌈
description: Agender lesbian menace. "The Last Starfighter" superfan. #ActuallyAutistic (she/her)
tweet: Make it a conversation. Our brains prioritize conversation over text. Talk out loud to the author. Argue. Ask questions. Answer questions posed by the author. Laugh at their jokes!

name: Julia Gulia 🏳️‍⚧️🏳️‍🌈
description: Agender lesbian menace. "The Last Starfighter" superfan. #ActuallyAutistic (she/her)
tweet: Don’t stop at one reading. You’re training your brain like you would at a new sport. Read the book once (even skimming is better than not reading) and then come back to it when you have stronger reading muscles. You’ll gain even more insights.

name: Julia Gulia 🏳️‍⚧️🏳️‍🌈
description: Agender lesbian menace. "The Last Starfighter" superfan. #ActuallyAutistic (she/her)
tweet: Don’t get discouraged - I mean it. Reading nonfiction/academic writing is hard. They give degrees to people who can write fancy! Give yourself the same grace you would when learning a second language and don’t quit. Do. Not. Quit.
